combative systems of both Europe

721
00:43:27,071 --> 00:43:28,561
and the ancient world.

722
00:43:28,672 --> 00:43:31,869
They have set out to practice
with a different kind of energy

723
00:43:31,976 --> 00:43:34,501
and intensity separate from
the reenactment

724
00:43:34,612 --> 00:43:37,638
and sport fencing groups.

725
00:43:37,748 --> 00:43:40,342
We're trying to discover
something that's always

726
00:43:40,451 --> 00:43:43,978
been there and has been
forgotten and it's a lot of work

727
00:43:44,088 --> 00:43:49,492
to obviously, to try to
understand what was lost.

728
00:43:50,828 --> 00:43:52,728
It's a part of
our history in Europe

729
00:43:52,830 --> 00:43:54,593
and I think that's
very important.

730
00:43:54,698 --> 00:43:56,393
This is actually
our history.

731
00:43:56,500 --> 00:43:59,867
This is actually
how we fought.

732
00:43:59,970 --> 00:44:02,495
Historical European
martial arts is the study

733
00:44:02,606 --> 00:44:07,168
of Europe's traditional
fighting systems.

734
00:44:07,277 --> 00:44:09,745
I'm doing this because
I had previously studied

735
00:44:09,847 --> 00:44:12,543
Asian martial arts and l
wanted to study martial arts

736
00:44:12,650 --> 00:44:15,517
related to my own culture
and the place that I'm from.

737
00:44:15,619 --> 00:44:18,554
Martial arts from Japan
or China or southeastAsia,

738
00:44:18,656 --> 00:44:20,681
as valid as they are,
I wanted something

739
00:44:20,791 --> 00:44:23,692
that was from
my culture and for me.

740
00:44:23,794 --> 00:44:26,888
I came from a long background of
doing martial arts so I wanted

741
00:44:26,997 --> 00:44:30,455
to see how modem arts compared
to the old arts and it seems

742
00:44:30,567 --> 00:44:33,593
that their standard was every
bit as complicated as ours,

743
00:44:33,704 --> 00:44:36,605
and possibly more so.

744
00:44:39,209 --> 00:44:42,178
If you look at modern sport
fencing and kendo, and the like,

745
00:44:42,279 --> 00:44:44,042
they've actually become
simplified versions

746
00:44:44,148 --> 00:44:48,585
of these great complex systems,
which are actually brutal.

747
00:44:48,686 --> 00:44:51,587
It's our past, it's
part of our culture actually.

748
00:44:53,557 --> 00:44:56,390
Today historical European
martial arts groups

749
00:44:56,493 --> 00:44:59,826
are reclaiming the ancient
fighting techniques

750
00:44:59,930 --> 00:45:06,335
and studying the diversity
of arms and armor.

751
00:45:08,839 --> 00:45:11,307
For me I think the sword
is like what it was

752
00:45:11,408 --> 00:45:12,966
in the medieval time.

753
00:45:13,077 --> 00:45:18,071
What matters is the man
on the other side.

754
00:45:20,084 --> 00:45:22,575
The difference between
the medieval sword

755
00:45:22,686 --> 00:45:24,119
and the Japanese sword

756
00:45:24,221 --> 00:45:26,849
is that the Japanese
put their soul into the sword.

757
00:45:26,957 --> 00:45:29,187
In medieval time,
what matters was

758
00:45:29,293 --> 00:45:31,523
to put the other man
into the sword.

759
00:45:31,628 --> 00:45:33,926
There's no such thing
as just a sword.

760
00:45:34,031 --> 00:45:35,498
It's a weapon
for killing people

761
00:45:35,599 --> 00:45:37,260
and I'm learning how
to do it efficiently.

762
00:45:37,367 --> 00:45:41,667
To me the sword is...

763
00:45:41,772 --> 00:45:43,672
cool.

764
00:45:45,609 --> 00:45:45,876
For centuries these
ancient fighting skills

765
00:45:45,876 --> 00:45:48,174
For centuries these
ancient fighting skills

766
00:45:48,278 --> 00:45:50,473
have not been practiced.

767
00:45:50,581 --> 00:45:54,312
Historical fencing students
are now leaming to reconstruct

768
00:45:54,418 --> 00:46:00,323
martial arts that have
been until now, extinct.

769
00:46:00,424 --> 00:46:02,153
We're having to try
and rediscover

770
00:46:02,259 --> 00:46:05,524
what the fight masters
of the time were thinking

771
00:46:05,629 --> 00:46:09,656
and how they formulated their
techniques and how they evolved.

772
00:46:09,767 --> 00:46:12,895
So there's quite a strong
academic side to it

773
00:46:13,003 --> 00:46:14,903
in the westem martial arts.

774
00:46:15,005 --> 00:46:18,406
We're essentially
resurrecting this from books.

775
00:46:18,509 --> 00:46:20,807
Just as European scholars
wrote down every other

776
00:46:20,911 --> 00:46:23,778
art and science,
the science of defense

777
00:46:23,881 --> 00:46:26,816
was also documented
and recorded.

778
00:46:26,917 --> 00:46:29,385
Many of the old
fighting manuals and treaties

779
00:46:29,486 --> 00:46:32,751
that were written during
the 15th and 16th centuries have

780
00:46:32,856 --> 00:46:37,850
recently been rediscovered and
are now being studied worldwide.

781
00:46:37,961 --> 00:46:40,395
We focus on mainly
German manuals

782
00:46:40,497 --> 00:46:46,436
but also ltalian manuals,
15th century and 16th century.

783
00:46:46,537 --> 00:46:49,062
My personal favorite
