937
00:54:53,056 --> 00:54:55,957
An iron core with
a forge-welded steel edge,

938
00:54:56,059 --> 00:54:59,392
so you get the flex
and strength of the iron

939
00:54:59,496 --> 00:55:02,590
with the extreme
cutting power of the steel.

940
00:55:02,699 --> 00:55:05,133
Which is incredibly tough and
quite springy and flexible,

941
00:55:05,235 --> 00:55:06,668
so it won't break
very easily.

942
00:55:06,770 --> 00:55:09,796
You'd rather have a sword
softer, take a set,

943
00:55:09,906 --> 00:55:12,101
take a bend, than break.

944
00:55:12,208 --> 00:55:13,732
Because a broken sword in
your hand during a battle,

945
00:55:13,843 --> 00:55:14,867
you're done.

946
00:55:14,978 --> 00:55:16,946
I wouldn't want to be the smith
that the customer came back to

947
00:55:17,047 --> 00:55:19,811
with his brother's broken
sword in his hand going,

948
00:55:19,916 --> 00:55:21,611
"Hey, why did you make
